42:33.974 --> 42:37.776
His dad bought him a gun
to toughen him up.

42:37.778 --> 42:39.244
That was the sanction he needed.

42:39.246 --> 42:43.449
Look, we need to get
to Simon's trigger memory.

42:43.451 --> 42:45.150
But how?

42:45.152 --> 42:47.954
I don't know yet.
I'm working on it.

42:47.956 --> 42:50.224
[PHONE BEEPS]

43:02.269 --> 43:05.070
Hi. Can we meet?

43:05.072 --> 43:06.808
Okay, see you soon.

43:16.550 --> 43:19.418
[GRUNTING]

43:19.420 --> 43:21.123
[FISTS THUDDING]

43:22.856 --> 43:25.126
[TENSE MUSIC]

43:41.909 --> 43:43.846
[GASPING]

43:57.291 --> 43:59.492
[TENSE MUSIC]

43:59.494 --> 44:01.930
[MACHINE BEEPING]

44:23.952 --> 44:25.450
RACHEL:
I was just giving him an update.

44:25.452 --> 44:28.489
And of course you would
be the one to update him.

44:32.860 --> 44:34.228
So, did you?

44:36.898 --> 44:38.063
Update him?

44:38.065 --> 44:39.398
Yes.

44:39.400 --> 44:41.200
I told him everything
was under control

44:41.202 --> 44:44.103
and that it was moving
forward as we planned.

44:44.105 --> 44:46.240
Is he?
Is he under control?

44:49.376 --> 44:50.878
Do you doubt me, Walter?

44:54.081 --> 44:56.048
Rachel, I'm very concerned.

44:56.050 --> 44:59.150
You're my friend
and I trust you.

44:59.152 --> 45:03.623
But you need to remember
that I am running a business

45:03.625 --> 45:07.228
and you can never forget
who you actually work for.

45:09.396 --> 45:11.165
You always come to me...

45:12.300 --> 45:13.502
first.

45:17.572 --> 45:19.541
[SIGHS]

45:30.150 --> 45:32.587
[SIREN WAILING]

45:44.197 --> 45:47.999
[SOFT PIANO MUSIC]

45:48.001 --> 45:50.137
You should talk to your wife.

45:52.206 --> 45:55.041
Really? And why is that?

45:55.043 --> 45:57.976
I'm no expert, but I believe
it has something to do

45:57.978 --> 46:00.211
with your insistence
on working late hours,

46:00.213 --> 46:02.650
ignoring all familial
responsibilities.

46:04.217 --> 46:06.385
Ah, familial. That's new.

46:06.387 --> 46:08.688
Uh, okay, guilty as charged.

46:08.690 --> 46:10.289
Um...

46:10.291 --> 46:12.661
any suggestions
on how I can fix the situation?

46:14.494 --> 46:16.063
Just talk to her.

46:21.202 --> 46:23.005
Well, thanks for your help.

46:44.224 --> 46:46.694
[SUBDUED MUSIC]

47:06.380 --> 47:08.447
[BELL RINGS]

47:08.449 --> 47:11.353
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

47:18.559 --> 47:21.163
[BELL RINGS]

47:35.809 --> 47:37.610
Hi, Adam.

47:37.612 --> 47:40.278
Sorry to bother you, but I
really have a lead on something.

47:40.280 --> 47:41.449
It's really late.

47:42.382 --> 47:43.617
Can we talk inside?

47:45.485 --> 47:46.621
Sure.

47:56.630 --> 48:00.066
So, this is where
the magic happens.

48:00.068 --> 48:01.333
Yeah.

48:01.335 --> 48:03.836
Um, sorry about the mess.

48:03.838 --> 48:05.537
No, no, it's fine.

48:05.539 --> 48:09.108
My place is just as bad,
minus the cake crumbs.

48:09.110 --> 48:10.378
Yeah, it reminds
me of Brittany.

48:14.614 --> 48:16.715
Oh, I miss this.

48:16.717 --> 48:18.583
Good old-fashioned
research and development

48:18.585 --> 48:23.555
before I got sucked into the
whole save the world campaign.

48:23.557 --> 48:24.824
Yep, science
is a beautiful thing.

48:24.826 --> 48:28.193
It's just questions and answers.

48:28.195 --> 48:32.398
No uncomfortable silences
you don't understand.

48:32.400 --> 48:34.769
Are you sure you're still
talking about science?

48:38.840 --> 48:40.342
I don't know, are we?

48:41.509 --> 48:42.740
This...

48:42.742 --> 48:44.309
This whole project...

48:44.311 --> 48:45.845
What are we essentially
doing here, Rachel?

48:45.847 --> 48:48.682
We are stripping away
the ability to make choices.

48:50.251 --> 48:52.617
My father had freedom of choice.

48:52.619 --> 48:55.156
And Simon.
Do you think he deserves it?

48:56.523 --> 48:58.791
Freedom of choice isn't
something to be stumbled upon.

48:58.793 --> 49:00.829
It is something to be deserved.

49:15.175 --> 49:16.342
You know, you better be careful.

49:16.344 --> 49:17.412
You're starting
to sound like him.

49:20.248 --> 49:23.585
Edward was good to me
when I did what I did.

49:25.853 --> 49:27.856
He gave me a fresh
start when I needed one.

49:29.657 --> 49:32.561
So, what were you working on?

49:41.202 --> 49:42.834
Trying to find a way
to program the nanobots

49:42.836 --> 49:46.338
into forming a chain
of interlocking events.

49:46.340 --> 49:47.706
Turns out they can
already do that.

49:47.708 --> 49:49.708
You see these green
wavelengths here?

49:49.710 --> 49:51.376
Well, they're
associated brain cells

49:51.378 --> 49:54.215
carrying the same
sort of memories.

49:55.483 --> 49:58.950
We need to show them
the light, if you will.

49:58.952 --> 50:00.853
I think I understand.

50:00.855 --> 50:02.287
You need to give
them a common theme

50:02.289 --> 50:03.655
to follow back into the past.

50:03.657 --> 50:04.826
Exactly.

50:08.262 --> 50:12.167
That is exactly why I'm here.

50:15.202 --> 50:16.769
- Really?
- I know.

50:16.771 --> 50:19.740
Um, close your eyes.

50:22.210 --> 50:23.345
Trust me.

50:25.913 --> 50:27.746
Now, I'm gonna say a word

50:27.748 --> 50:30.749
and you say the first
word that comes to mind.

50:30.751 --> 50:33.321
Just close your eyes, okay?

50:34.621 --> 50:37.458
We'll start with work.

50:39.260 --> 50:40.626
Don't think too hard about it.

50:40.628 --> 50:42.394
Just the first thing
that comes to mind.

50:42.396 --> 50:43.498
Okay.

50:44.465 --> 50:45.530
Research.

50:45.532 --> 50:46.599
Fun.

50:46.601 --> 50:47.865
Work.

50:47.867 --> 50:48.934
Exhausting.

50:48.936 --> 50:50.469
Nanobots.

50:50.471 --> 50:51.769
The future.

50:51.771 --> 50:52.871
The future.

50:52.873 --> 50:54.340
Peaceful.

50:54.342 --> 50:55.376
Peaceful.

50:56.344 --> 50:57.809
Family.

50:57.811 --> 50:58.876
Family?

50:58.878 --> 50:59.945
Marie.

50:59.947 --> 51:01.646
Marie.

51:01.648 --> 51:02.817
Brittany.

51:04.885 --> 51:07.485
And if what you said
is true and the brain

51:07.487 --> 51:09.755
stores memories
in categories of feelings,

51:09.757 --> 51:13.758
if we give those feelings
to the nanobots to follow.

51:13.760 --> 51:15.793
It'll show them
how to take it back...

51:15.795 --> 51:18.296
- To the trigger memory.
- Trigger memories, of course.

51:18.298 --> 51:19.831
That's genius.

51:19.833 --> 51:21.499
If we hit him with the
end of his violent episodes,

51:21.501 --> 51:23.601
that's the feeling
he's trying to recreate.

51:23.603 --> 51:25.673
That would bring us right back
to the first time.

51:27.007 --> 51:28.474
Where are we going?

51:28.476 --> 51:29.675
Your place.

51:29.677 --> 51:31.880
- You mean the lab.
- Of course.

51:39.786 --> 51:42.854
Look, I know it's late,
but I think we've...

51:42.856 --> 51:44.423
Are you sure you wanna go now?

51:44.425 --> 51:45.961
We could always take
this up tomorrow.

51:54.367 --> 51:55.536
Let's go now.

52:04.778 --> 52:06.880
[ELECTRONIC WHIRR]

52:10.818 --> 52:12.754
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

52:14.954 --> 52:16.357
[THUD]

52:22.963 --> 52:26.668
[WHISTLING]

52:29.769 --> 52:31.472
[YELLS]

52:32.806 --> 52:35.576
[SIMON GRUNTING]

52:37.811 --> 52:39.447
[YELLS]

52:41.815 --> 52:44.615
Wipe that smirk off your face.

52:44.617 --> 52:46.788
Once again,
you've jeopardized everything.

52:53.728 --> 52:55.297
Yeah, it's me.

52:56.530 --> 52:57.832
Yes, again.

52:58.998 --> 53:00.334
I know.

53:01.735 --> 53:03.003
Thanks.

53:12.112 --> 53:14.014
[ELECTRONIC WHIRR]

53:15.882 --> 53:17.951
You're sure no one saw you?

53:30.831 --> 53:31.932
Bags.

53:34.068 --> 53:35.937
[ELECTRONIC WHIRR]

53:57.425 --> 53:59.928
[ELECTRONIC WHIRR]

54:06.833 --> 54:07.969
Your mother...

54:09.503 --> 54:11.503
as low as they come.

54:11.505 --> 54:12.840
She's gone for good now.

54:17.710 --> 54:19.646
Don't ever believe women.

54:20.748 --> 54:22.583
Their hearts are evil.

54:23.818 --> 54:25.184
Like...

54:25.186 --> 54:28.954
Like a slow poison,
they get in your veins

54:28.956 --> 54:31.059
and then they ruin you.

54:33.059 --> 54:34.795
Mark my words.

54:38.865 --> 54:40.532
[ELECTRONIC WHIRR]

54:40.534 --> 54:42.804
His mother's disappearance
wasn't reason enough.

54:44.204 --> 54:46.104
It was Edward.

54:46.106 --> 54:47.505
Edward's the trigger.

54:47.507 --> 54:49.740
We can't assume
that Senator Frost

54:49.742 --> 54:52.677
is the sole cause
of all of his actions.

54:52.679 --> 54:55.046
Rachel, he knew
what he was up to.

54:55.048 --> 54:57.851
You saw. He kept Simon safe.
This...

55:00.521 --> 55:01.787
This whole experiment's
been a coverup.

55:01.789 --> 55:02.887
We need to tell Walter.

55:02.889 --> 55:03.791
No.

55:04.992 --> 55:07.626
That would jeopardize
the entire project.

55:07.628 --> 55:10.162
How can we expect
a rational scientific outcome

55:10.164 --> 55:12.965
if this whole thing's
been manipulated from the start?

55:12.967 --> 55:14.532
Adam.

55:14.534 --> 55:15.666
Adam, please.

55:15.668 --> 55:16.804
Adam.

55:17.905 --> 55:19.938
- Walter.
- Ah.

55:19.940 --> 55:21.940
Dr. Anderson,
I'm so glad you could join us.

55:21.942 --> 55:25.079
I was just briefing the senator
on your remarkable progress.

55:31.217 --> 55:34.253
So, Doctors...

55:34.255 --> 55:37.555
your deadline has come and gone.
What's the good news?

55:37.557 --> 55:38.927
We need more time.

55:41.594 --> 55:44.262
I think what Rachel
is intending to say

55:44.264 --> 55:47.932
is that they have acquired
some excellent data

55:47.934 --> 55:50.601
and that now it is simply a
matter of having it reconfirmed.

55:50.603 --> 55:52.606
It's all good! Let's drink.

55:53.806 --> 55:55.509
Some more time.

55:57.677 --> 55:59.244
Hmm.

55:59.246 --> 56:02.713
So, that looking through
past memories for answers

56:02.715 --> 56:05.784
was a complete waste of my time.

56:05.786 --> 56:08.052
I'm sure you'd
like to think so.

56:08.054 --> 56:09.156
Well...

56:10.224 --> 56:12.193
we'll have to agree to disagree,
huh?

56:14.228 --> 56:15.496
Now...

56:16.797 --> 56:18.697
have you ever looked above

56:18.699 --> 56:22.166
or beyond your
little universe, hmm?

56:22.168 --> 56:24.505
The world is falling apart.

56:25.806 --> 56:28.907
Violence has gotten
into every crevice of society

56:28.909 --> 56:30.608
and we need to control it.

56:30.610 --> 56:32.043
I know what you know,

56:32.045 --> 56:34.681
and I'm gonna make sure
everyone else knows, too.

56:40.054 --> 56:42.820
I'd like to have a word
with Adam.

56:42.822 --> 56:44.025
Alone.

56:45.025 --> 56:46.126
Please.

56:48.896 --> 56:49.998
Rachel.

57:00.039 --> 57:01.308
[DOOR CLOSES]

57:02.710 --> 57:06.047
So, what is it?

57:08.047 --> 57:09.615
What?

57:09.617 --> 57:11.916
The trigger memory.

57:11.918 --> 57:14.653
How do you know about
the trigger memory?

57:14.655 --> 57:16.224
How do I know?

57:18.391 --> 57:19.927
It's irrelevant.

57:23.163 --> 57:27.065
Your wife, his mother.
What you said.

57:27.067 --> 57:28.570
I loved my wife...

57:30.204 --> 57:32.003
very much.

57:32.005 --> 57:33.905
Much like you loved yours.

57:33.907 --> 57:35.843
I still do and I always will.

57:38.077 --> 57:40.244
So who's gonna
listen to you then?

57:40.246 --> 57:41.979
The media, the authorities.

57:41.981 --> 57:42.750
Ah, right.

57:44.150 --> 57:48.956
The mad scientist with the
magical memory technology, hmm?

57:50.958 --> 57:52.894
It's your word against mine.

58:06.840 --> 58:08.142
Let me tell you something.

58:11.878 --> 58:16.148
I used to be a detective
a long time ago.

58:16.150 --> 58:17.818
Of course, you know that.

58:19.186 --> 58:20.922
I worked the streets.

58:21.889 --> 58:23.391
I was very happy.

58:24.858 --> 58:26.361
Do you love your work?

58:29.262 --> 58:30.197
Me, too.

58:31.364 --> 58:36.367
But my wife, she was
obsessed with ambition.

58:36.369 --> 58:37.638
Not hers, mine.

58:39.005 --> 58:41.206
She was always telling me,
"You're better than that job."

58:41.208 --> 58:46.711
And what I called stable,
she called stagnant.

58:46.713 --> 58:48.880
Now, I...

58:48.882 --> 58:50.818
I loved my wife.

58:52.286 --> 58:57.125
I really loved her.

58:59.992 --> 59:00.994
But it...

59:02.128 --> 59:04.731
wasn't enough
to make her feel special.

59:07.800 --> 59:10.302
So anyway, one day I came home

59:10.304 --> 59:12.503
and she was nagging at me
to meet the mayor.

59:12.505 --> 59:14.905
She was sitting
on some committee with him.

59:14.907 --> 59:18.209
And I thought, okay, why not?

59:18.211 --> 59:20.177
What have I got to lose?

59:20.179 --> 59:23.014
Maybe it's time for a change.

59:23.016 --> 59:25.751
So the next morning
I got into my finest suit,

59:25.753 --> 59:27.318
didn't say a word to Susan,

59:27.320 --> 59:30.454
and I headed down
to the mayor's office.

59:30.456 --> 59:33.992
So I'm at the mayor's office
and he's not available.

59:33.994 --> 59:38.463
So I figure I'll wait, you know,
catch him between appointments.

59:38.465 --> 59:42.233
I'm there for
about an hour or so.

59:42.235 --> 59:44.038
I'm thinking I should leave.

59:45.271 --> 59:46.840
And...

59:48.175 --> 59:53.448
And then I think about how
proud it would make my wife.

59:56.349 --> 59:58.282
And then...

59:58.284 --> 59:59.820
there she is.

01:00:00.521 --> 01:00:02.789
Smiling, hair tousled.

01:00:04.190 --> 01:00:06.259
His hand on her waist.

01:00:08.427 --> 01:00:11.498
I couldn't tell you who was more
dumbstruck to see the other one.

01:00:14.333 --> 01:00:19.139
But I took advantage
of our situation.

01:00:20.474 --> 01:00:25.510
And that's where I learned
how power really works.

01:00:25.512 --> 01:00:27.112
And now here you are.

01:00:27.114 --> 01:00:29.380
And now here I am.

01:00:29.382 --> 01:00:31.251
And my wife...

01:00:32.286 --> 01:00:33.788
she's gone.

01:00:34.855 --> 01:00:39.157
I am always,
always moving forward.

01:00:39.159 --> 01:00:41.429
I try and stay
ahead of the pack.

01:00:42.996 --> 01:00:45.229
The past is the past.

01:00:45.231 --> 01:00:46.099
Can't hurt me.

01:00:49.168 --> 01:00:53.039
If you dwell on it,
you'll become stagnant.

01:00:55.007 --> 01:00:56.176
So...

01:01:00.213 --> 01:01:02.048
Five days, Dr. Anderson.

01:01:04.050 --> 01:01:07.889
I suggest you start
moving forward, too.

01:01:42.588 --> 01:01:44.424
You've gotta keep going.

01:01:45.925 --> 01:01:46.927
You know I can't.

01:01:48.929 --> 01:01:50.494
Jesus, this thing was hopeless
from the beginning.

01:01:50.496 --> 01:01:52.363
I don't know
why I was wasting my time.

01:01:52.365 --> 01:01:53.664
You weren't wasting your time.

01:01:53.666 --> 01:01:55.599
You were actually trying
to help the cause.

01:01:55.601 --> 01:01:57.202
The cause?

01:01:57.204 --> 01:01:58.470
What?
The cause to what?

01:01:58.472 --> 01:02:00.237
To stop violence
when you've got people

01:02:00.239 --> 01:02:02.442
like Frost Sr.
running the system?

01:02:04.443 --> 01:02:05.179
Jesus...

01:02:06.380 --> 01:02:08.313
Sometimes I feel like,
in some twisted way,

01:02:08.315 --> 01:02:10.148
they wanna keep
the violence alive.

01:02:10.150 --> 01:02:11.548
That way they can invent and
implement cures just like ours.

01:02:11.550 --> 01:02:13.320
They can just...
they can just...

01:02:17.257 --> 01:02:19.260
You're probably right.

01:02:22.094 --> 01:02:25.296
- He covered for me once, too...
- Stop blaming yourself.

01:02:25.298 --> 01:02:28.365
[SOFT PIANO MUSIC]

01:02:28.367 --> 01:02:29.503
Look.

01:02:30.670 --> 01:02:33.039
You were trying
to protect your mother.

01:02:34.574 --> 01:02:36.708
Rachel, don't you see
how you're being manipulated?

01:02:36.710 --> 01:02:40.114
It was an accident
and he's making you feel guilt.

01:02:43.516 --> 01:02:45.285
You're not like them.

01:02:50.356 --> 01:02:53.094
Only he could fear the weight
of an accusation.

01:02:58.164 --> 01:02:59.367
Thank you.

01:03:09.076 --> 01:03:10.144
Adam.

01:03:13.079 --> 01:03:14.248
You should...

01:03:16.449 --> 01:03:18.118
you should go home.

01:03:20.052 --> 01:03:23.190
You'll find everything
you need there.

01:03:47.780 --> 01:03:50.250
[SIREN WAILING]

01:03:58.324 --> 01:03:59.523
I know what you did!

01:03:59.525 --> 01:04:01.328
MAN:
Yeah, I fucking did it.

01:04:03.797 --> 01:04:06.164
What the fuck
you looking at, huh?

01:04:06.166 --> 01:04:08.333
[TIRES SQUEALING]

01:04:08.335 --> 01:04:09.603
[THUDS]

01:04:10.637 --> 01:04:12.269
[GASPING]

01:04:12.271 --> 01:04:14.007
MAN: What the fuck
you looking at, huh?

01:04:24.550 --> 01:04:27.385
Uh, hello everyone
out there in T.V. land.

01:04:27.387 --> 01:04:30.655
<i>Today is our weird
daughter's tenth birthday.</i>

01:04:30.657 --> 01:04:32.490
<i>And being her annoying parents,</i>

01:04:32.492 --> 01:04:34.425
<i>we got her the cheesiest
number 10 we could find.</i>

01:04:34.427 --> 01:04:36.193
- <i>Say hello, honey.</i>
- <i>Hello, honey.</i>

01:04:36.195 --> 01:04:38.128
<i>Nice. Um...</i>

01:04:38.130 --> 01:04:41.365
<i>So, we've gotten her what
she wanted for her birthday,</i>

01:04:41.367 --> 01:04:46.170
<i>but we're going to ease her
into the surprise.</i>

01:04:46.172 --> 01:04:48.238
- <i>Get that.</i>
- <i>[LAUGHS] Higher.</i>

01:04:48.240 --> 01:04:49.641
<i>Get your butt up there.</i>

01:04:49.643 --> 01:04:52.213
<i>Quiet, she's sleeping.</i>

01:04:53.713 --> 01:04:55.416
<i>Here we go.</i>

01:04:57.583 --> 01:04:59.486
<i>One, two, three.</i>

01:05:00.387 --> 01:05:04.322
BOTH:
<i>Happy birthday!</i>

01:05:04.324 --> 01:05:06.724
<i>What time is it?</i>

01:05:06.726 --> 01:05:08.695
<i>Time to get up, honey bunny.</i>

01:05:12.164 --> 01:05:13.768
She's gone, Marie.

01:05:15.469 --> 01:05:17.605
I can't go on
like this anymore.

01:05:19.271 --> 01:05:23.576
Every day, I'm trying
to run away from this...

01:05:25.378 --> 01:05:27.148
pain and I can't do it.

01:05:28.547 --> 01:05:30.615
<i>Really? I thought you loved it,
with the bouncy castle...</i>

01:05:30.617 --> 01:05:32.219
I feel like I'm chasing...

01:05:33.586 --> 01:05:36.153
<i>The Horror Show? You guys bought
me tickets to The Horror Show?</i>

01:05:36.155 --> 01:05:38.255
ADAM: I don't even know
what I'm chasing anymore.

